# Shelby Leaderboard API

A simple REST API that demonstrates how wallet contribution rankings could be implemented for the Shelby ecosystem.

This API exposes endpoints that return wallet rankings based on contribution scores.

---

## Demo

Run the API

```
npm start
```

Request endpoint

```
http://localhost:3000/leaderboard
```

Example response

```
[
  { "wallet": "0x123", "score": 210 },
  { "wallet": "0xabc", "score": 180 },
  { "wallet": "0x999", "score": 150 }
]
```

---

## Features

• REST API server
• Wallet contribution leaderboard
• Express.js backend
• Expandable scoring system

---

## Quick Install

```
curl -sL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YOURNAME/shelby-leaderboard-api/main/install.sh | bash
```

Manual install

```
git clone https://github.com/YOURNAME/shelby-leaderboard-api
cd shelby-leaderboard-api
npm install
```

Run

```
npm start
```

